headlines.description: — Cole Anthony made the tiebreaking layup with 45 seconds left, and the Orlando Magic squandered a 23-point lead before edging the Cleveland Cavaliers 109-104 on Wednesday night to snap a six-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic squander 23-point lead in fourth, beat Cavs 109-104

headlines.description: — Seth Curry scored 20 points, Tobias Harris and Joel Embiid each added 17 and the Philadelphia 76ers built a big early lead and cruised to a 127-83 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night to clinch an Eastern Conference playoff berth.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers rout Hawks 127-83 to clinch playoff spot

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Still missing LeBron James, the Los Angeles Lakers lost for the fourth time in their past five games Wednesday night, beaten 116-107 by the Washington Wizards, who got league scoring leader Bradley Beal's 27 points and Russell Westbrook's 13th...
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal, Westbrook lead Wizards past LeBron-less Lakers 116-107

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 38 points, Jayson Tatum added 35, and the Boston Celtics rebounded from an embarrassing loss a night earlier with a 120-111 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics rebound behind Brown, Tatum, beat Hornets 120-111

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 34 points and the New York Knicks beat the Chicago Bulls 113-94 on Wednesday night for their 10th win in 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Knicks beat Bulls 113-94 for 10th win in 11 games

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Erik Spoelstra got a milestone win, and it didn’t come easily.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spoelstra gets win No. 600, Heat top Spurs 116-111

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum had 26 points and six assists, and Norman Powell added 24 points, helping the Portland Trail Blazers solidify their hold on seventh place in the West with a 130-109 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Powell help Trail Blazers defeat Grizzlies 130-109

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 32 points and blocked Zion Williamson's shot from behind with 2.2 seconds remaining as the Denver Nuggets keep rolling even without standout point guard Jamal Murray, holding off the New Orleans Pelicans 114-112 Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic blocks late shot, Nuggets hold off Pelicans 114-112

headlines.description: — Chris Paul scored 28 points, Devin Booker added 21 and the Phoenix Suns beat the Los Angeles Clippers 109-101 on Wednesday night to clinch a spot in the playoffs for the first time in 11 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns beat Clippers, clinch first playoff spot in 11 years

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 24 points, Utah made 24 3-pointers, and the short-handed Jazz bounced back from consecutive losses and set a franchise scoring record in a 154-105 win over the Sacramento Kings on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rout Kings 154-105, snap two-game losing streak
